                  </extent>
                  <foliation type="ancient"/>
                  <collation>
                    <p>The quires are now only 4 in number. What the original signatures were, is not apparent.</p>
                  </collation>
                  <condition>
                    <list>
                      <item>
                        <p>Some of the leaves are much stained and torn, especially foll. <locus from="1" to="5">1—5</locus>, <locus from="9">9</locus>, <locus from="12">12</locus> and <locus from="23">23</locus>.</p>
                      </item>
                      <item>
                        <p>Of the quires the 3d and 4th are very imperfect, leaves being wanting after foll. 22, 26 and 28.</p>
                      </item>
                    </list>
                  </condition>
                </supportDesc>
                <layoutDesc>
                  <layout columns="2" writtenLines="28 33">
                    <p>Each page is divided into two columns, of from 28 to 33 lines.</p>
                  </layout>
                </layoutDesc>
              </objectDesc>
              <handDesc hands="7">
                <handNote xml:id="handNote1" scope="major" script="syr-Syre" medium="unknown">
                  <desc>The writing is a good, regular Estrangela of the <origDate notBefore="0500" notAfter="0600" calendar="Gregorian">vith cent</origDate>.</desc>
                </handNote>
                <handNote xml:id="handNote2" scope="minor" script="syr" medium="unknown">
                  <desc><ref target="#addition1">See additions.</ref></desc>
                </handNote>
                <handNote xml:id="handNote3" scope="minor" script="unknown" medium="unknown">
                  <desc><ref target="#addition2">See additions.</ref></desc>
                </handNote>
                <handNote xml:id="handNote4" scope="minor" script="cop" medium="unknown">
                  <desc><ref target="#addition3">See additions.</ref></desc>
                </handNote>
                <handNote xml:id="handNote5" scope="minor" script="grc" medium="unknown">
                  <desc><ref target="#addition4">See additions.</ref></desc>
                </handNote>
                <handNote xml:id="handNote6" scope="minor" script="syr" medium="unknown">
                  <desc><ref target="#addition5">See additions.</ref></desc>
                </handNote>
                <handNote xml:id="handNote7" scope="minor" script="syr" medium="unknown">
                  <desc><ref target="#addition6">See additions.</ref></desc>
                </handNote>
              </handDesc>
              <decoDesc/>
              <additions>
                <p/>
                <list>
                  <item n="1" xml:id="addition1">
                    <ref target="#handNote2"/>
                    <p>Later hands have marked the quires with letters.</p>
                  </item>
                  <item n="2" xml:id="addition2">
                    <ref target="#handNote3"/>
                    <p>Later hands have marked the quires with arithmetical figures.</p>
                  </item>
                  <item n="3" xml:id="addition3">
                    <ref target="#handNote4"/>
                    <p>One reader has numbered the pages with Coptic ciphers (on the verso at the top).</p>
                  </item>
                  <item n="4" xml:id="addition4">
                    <ref target="#handNote5"/>
                    <p>A few Greek vowels have been added by a later hand.</p>
                  </item>
                  <item n="5" xml:id="addition5">
                    <locus from="3a"/>
                    <ref target="#handNote6"/>
                    <p>On fol. 3a there are the remains of a note, showing that this was one of the 250 volumes, procured for the <placeName>convent of S. Mary Deipara</placeName> by the <persName>abbat Moses of Nisibis</persName>, A. Gr. <date when-custom="1243" datingMethod="Seleucid">1243</date>, A.D. <date when="0932" calendar="Gregorian">932</date>.</p>
                  </item>
                  <item n="6" xml:id="addition6">
                    <locus from="2a" to="2b"/>
                    <ref target="#handNote7"/>
                    <p>The torn leaf fol. 2 seems to contain fragments of a hymn, of later date.</p>
                  </item>
                </list>
              </additions>
